Mem. i 3, 5; Porphyr. de abst. iii 26. contentius: Nonius, p. 264 M. quotes this passage in support of the meaning of continuus, perseuerans given to contentus.

ξ 98. philitiis: the common meals (συσσίτια) of the Spartans were known as φιδίτια or φιλίτια, the latter form being no doubt due to a popular deriva- tion from φίλος; on the derivation of φιδίτια see (for different views) Vanicek, Elym. Wb'rt. p. 1010 ; Gilbert, Gk. Const. Antz'q. p. 66¹.
